description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hampshire cares, could you?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Malmesbury Lawn has excitingopportunitiesfor &lt;strong&gt;Care Assistants&lt;/strong&gt; to join our friendly and supportive team. We provide Nursing and Residential care and support to the elderly and vulnerable, so to succeed in this role you will have an empathy with the needs of older people and understand the importance of treating them with dignity and respect.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You may be an experienced &lt;strong&gt;Carer&lt;/strong&gt; or &lt;strong&gt;Support Worker&lt;/strong&gt; but this is not essential because in these vital roles,&lt;strong&gt; life experience is more important than work experience.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will give you all the support, training and development you will need to help you enjoy an extremely satisfying career in social care. The work can be challenging, but the rewards are beyond measure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you share our person-centred values and feel you can help to make our care home a place that our residents can really call home, we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hampshire County Council recognises the outstanding contribution our care staff make, so we offer a generous benefits package including;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A minimum 24 days annual leave entitlement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to Local Government Pension Scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest free travel loans and discounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Family friendly policies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
